Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.50,0:11:37.92,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fs70\fad(777,0)\blur5\c&H000000&\b1\t(0,400,\blur1)\pos(640,54)}Hyouka
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.01,0:11:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If one considers mysteries to be a duel between the writer and the reader,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.18,0:11:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,a mere dilettante such as Hongou barely counts as an opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.51,0:11:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we heard she wasn't familiar with mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.43,0:11:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Those books were her crash course into that enigmatic realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.27,0:12:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Prior to this film, she knew nothing about mystery, not even via graphic novels or cinema.{he seems like the kind of person who would say 'graphic novels'}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.53,0:12:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's Nobuhara's translation! A new edition as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.28,0:12:03.86,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.7\fax-0.02\fs20\fnArial Rounded MT\c&H737176&\frz349.8\frx12\fry0\org(837,242)\pos(649,217)}The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.28,0:12:03.86,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fscx90\blur0.7\fax-0.02\fs18\fnAubrey PL\c&HC88C5A&\frz349.8\frx12\fry0\org(849,284)\pos(632,253)}Conan Doyle / Translated by Nobuhara Ken
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.53,0:12:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She tried learning about mystery through Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.87,0:12:11.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Precisely! What a total amateur, I say!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.75,0:12:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.09,0:12:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oreki, Oreki!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.01,0:12:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There's some weird code here! Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.84,0:12:27.85,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur1\fs35\fnKingashandwriting\b1\c&H525453&\frz306\move(972,175,990,96,29,2990)}The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes\N\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hConan Doyle\N\NA Scandal in Bohemia\N\N\N\NThe Red-Headed League\N\N\NA Case of Identity\N\N\NThe Boscombe Valley Mystery\N\N\NThe Five Orange Pips\N\N\NThe Man with the Twisted Lip\N\N\NThe Blue Carbuncle\N\NThe Speckled Band\N\N\NA Case of Identity{yeah, again}\N\NThe Copper Beeches
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.10,0:12:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, here too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.89,0:12:32.85,signs,,0,0,0,,{\1a20\blur1\fs45\fnKingashandwriting\b1\c&H2A3131&\frz275\move(1128,330,1175,294,27,1945)}The Case-Book of Sherlock Holmes\N\N\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hConan Doyle\N\NThe Illustrious Client\N\N\NThe Blanched Soldier\N\N\NThe Mazarin Stone\N\N\NThe Three Gables\N\N\NThe Sussex Vampire\N\N\NThe Three Garridebs\N\NThe Problem of Thor Bridge\N\N\NThe Creeping Man\N\NThe Lion's Mane\N\N\NThe Veiled Lodger
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.11,0:12:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,She probably just marked off the ideas she could use.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.19,0:12:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.69,0:12:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Putting that aside,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.03,0:12:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,why don't we get down to brass tacks?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.41,0:12:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the floor plan?
