Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.70,0:12:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I've marked the characters as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.24,0:12:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please tell us your theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.91,0:12:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,By my assessment, this mystery is not difficult at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.87,0:12:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's really quite simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.09,0:12:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.13,0:13:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This murder wasn't planned in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.72,0:13:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, the culprit merely struck when the time was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.68,0:13:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.51,0:13:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Had it been planned, how would he relocate Kaitou to the left wing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.06,0:13:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaitou proceeded alone to the right side of the theater after choosing that key himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.15,0:13:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, this was a locked room murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.15,0:13:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All possible escape routes were secured and the only one left viable, the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.74,0:13:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,showed no signs of use.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.04,0:13:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,To wit: Kaitou's murderer could not escape via any normal means.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.58,0:13:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,As for whether he could have simply taken and returned the master key...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.13,0:13:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{kore wa}A conclusion as vapid as it is fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.13,0:13:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To retrieve the master key from the office, one would need to cross the entrance lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.14,0:13:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Any one of the characters could easily witness someone doing so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.43,0:13:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, not one of them could safely enter the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.06,0:14:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And not just the office, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.77,0:14:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire right-hand corridor that leads to the left wing was accessible by none.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.36,0:14:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ergo, this area is vital.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.91,0:14:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it means the culprit couldn't have approached the locked room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.50,0:14:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well... Essentially, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.04,0:14:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Likewise, the victim himself could not have locked the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.05,0:14:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What else is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.97,0:14:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor could he have been murdered through mechanical means, or after the door had been opened.{早業殺人}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.51,0:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,He was quite clearly dead, with his arm severed from his body.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.97,0:14:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, the solution to Hongou's locked room mystery is something other than the obvious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.06,0:14:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think? You're Oreki, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,How would you solve this locked room mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.32,0:14:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I dunno.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.16,0:14:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh please, that simply won't do!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.75,0:14:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't say I'm all that surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.00,0:14:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.16,0:15:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm on the prop team, as you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.08,0:15:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hongou instructed us to procure a rope that wouldn't snap under a person's weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.05,0:15:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand its purpose?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.05,0:15:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like I always say,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.22,0:15:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,if you can't enter via the first floor, try the second!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.52,0:15:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Kounosu was there on the second floor's right-hand corridor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.52,0:15:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Though she may seem delicate to you, she is in fact in the Mountaineering Club.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.31,0:15:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,She lowered the rope from the second floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.82,0:15:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,slew Kaitou from where he stood in the left wing,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.28,0:15:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and used that very same means of escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.24,0:15:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Were I to select a title for the movie, I'd call it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.08,0:15:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,"Invisible Entrance", or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.20,0:15:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, your opinions please.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.62,0:15:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Did Hongou ask you for anything besides the rope?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.71,0:15:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Not really. But she didn't always order everything she required.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.59,0:15:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,For instance, the volume of blood she had us prepare was not nearly enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.39,0:15:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so we had to go to some lengths to make more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.02,0:16:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything else? If that is all...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.31,0:16:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.27,0:16:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.23,0:16:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Just wondering,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.48,0:16:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,have you seen what's done of the movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.65,0:16:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I confess that I have not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.49,0:16:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He pisses me off!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.45,0:16:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.62,0:16:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,His attitude! Were you okay with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.12,0:16:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He even made fun of Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.00,0:16:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.00,0:16:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Holmes {\i1}is{\i0} aimed at beginners.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.09,0:16:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And it does seem like Hongou is a beginner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.34,0:16:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.97,0:16:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do you think of Haba's theory?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.51,0:16:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it sort of works.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.39,0:16:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a very interesting twist, but Hongou ordering that rope is pretty decisive.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.23,0:16:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a problem with it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.52,0:16:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.90,0:16:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't accept that theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.24,0:16:56.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Like with Nakajou's, something just feels off about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.45,0:17:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really know why, but I doubt Hongou was planning something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.21,0:17:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't you had enough of those?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.29,0:17:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? When did I have that many?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.13,0:17:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They tasted so interesting, I couldn't stop thinking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.76,0:17:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.72,0:17:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm all right! All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.81,0:17:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oreki, do you think his theory is correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.73,0:17:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.73,0:17:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If we were talking about a real murder, it might work,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.44,0:17:37.70,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fax0.07\blur0.5\fs25\fnArial Rounded MT\c&H5B5A5D&\frz84.69\pos(483,309)}The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.44,0:17:37.70,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fax0.07\blur0.5\fs20\fnAubrey PL\c&HCFCC9B&\frz85.73\pos(546,314)}Conan Doyle / Translated by Nobuhara Ken
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.90,0:17:36.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but it can't have been used in this movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.86,0:17:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.32,0:17:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's at odds with the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.33,0:17:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. The window, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.37,0:17:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It hadn't been touched for years, and didn't fit properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.21,0:17:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It took Katsuta some real effort just to get it open.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.67,0:17:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It creaked quite badly, not to mention it opens upward.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.46,0:17:58.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be almost impossible to quietly open a window like that while hanging on a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.64,0:18:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And would Kaitou just stand by and watch while she rattled away at the window?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.14,0:18:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't be that stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.39,0:18:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why you asked him if he'd seen the movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.81,0:18:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hongou surveyed the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.48,0:18:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If the window was a key part of the plot, she would've checked that as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.19,0:18:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But this wasn't reflected in the video,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.86,0:18:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so we can conclude that Hongou didn't care about the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.99,0:18:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I shouldn't have just said yes without thinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.17,0:18:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.96,0:18:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No good.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.92,0:18:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.71,0:18:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I've brought you the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.76,0:18:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
