Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.48,0:20:14.48,notebook,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6\pos(1032,349)}Two persons suggested (Hongou has final say)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.94,0:20:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,For them, mystery and horror are the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.78,0:20:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And nobody like, entered the room that Kaitou died in, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.16,0:20:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's gotta be a seventh person! It's obvious!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.16,0:20:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A seventh person?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.29,0:20:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hongou was looking for a seventh person besides the six actors.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.17,0:20:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,As the characters start to distrust each other more and more,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.04,0:20:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,they start seeing a slasher around every corner! And then a real one appears!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.01,0:20:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,A slasher?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.18,0:20:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I dunno how many of them would end up dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.56,0:20:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably all of them except one couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Then that couple would fend off the killer,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.02,0:20:54.19,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,170)\blur2\fs120\fnFrom Where You Are\pos(477,248)\frx28\fry356\org(535,248)\frz351.2\c&H2B160E&}Care
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.48,0:20:54.81,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(190,140)\blur2\fs120\fnFrom Where You Are\pos(477,248)\frx28\fry356\org(535,248)\frz351.2\c&H2B160E&}Care
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.02,0:20:55.31,signs,,0,0,0,,{\fad(190,140)\blur2\fs120\fnFrom Where You Are\pos(477,248)\frx28\fry356\org(535,248)\frz351.2\c&H2B160E&}Care
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.35,0:20:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and it'd all be over with a kiss lit by the rising sun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.32,0:20:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The title could be like,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,"Bloody Beast" or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.28,0:21:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Dunno, I guess that'd be kinda lame?{tehepero}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.32,0:21:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's something you guys could believe, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.66,0:21:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But what about the room of the murder?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.66,0:21:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It was locked, after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.54,0:21:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares about a lock or two?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.71,0:21:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Horror movie slashers never have any trouble with that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.63,0:21:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise... Oh, right! How about a vengeful spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.68,0:21:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That'd work too!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.93,0:21:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! Not a chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.10,0:21:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawakiguchi's theory definitely isn't what Hongou had in mind!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.85,0:21:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.60,0:21:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still not sure if this is a joke or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.69,0:21:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you refute it? Using logic only.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.77,0:21:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.44,0:21:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I said "using logic".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.74,0:21:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But wrong is wrong!{wrong things are wrong}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.41,0:21:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.29,0:21:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a kaleidoscope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.37,0:21:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Kaleidoscope?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.83,0:22:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Chi!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.92,0:22:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.18,0:22:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,She's asleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.97,0:22:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I did like how daring Sawakiguchi's theory was.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.81,0:22:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.11,0:22:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately, it's not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.07,0:22:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.11,0:22:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw how elaborate the script was, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.36,0:22:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,If Hongou wanted it to turn into a horror film halfway through,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.99,0:22:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,she would've at least listed the necessary props.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.37,0:22:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And what does a horror film need most?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.25,0:22:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What {\i1}does{\i0} it need most?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.46,0:22:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.25,0:22:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Haba mentioned it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.04,0:22:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hongou only asked for a little bit of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.21,0:22:52.01,signs,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5\fs60\fad(446,0)\fnLinux Libertine\b1\c&HE9E9EA&\pos(977,236)}As he tried to awaken \NKaitou, Sugimura\N  realized his hands \Nwere covered in {\c&H271D84&}{red}blood{\c&HE9E9E8&}{/red}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.51,0:22:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The script is also written under that assumption.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.92,0:22:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Which means Hongou wasn't planning some kind of bloodbath.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.01,0:22:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. It wouldn't be much of a horror movie with only one death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.47,0:22:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything has a reason, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.02,0:23:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.11,0:23:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.86,0:23:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi, get a hold of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.37,0:23:20.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, we refuted all their theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.87,0:23:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What'll happen to the movie now?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.63,0:23:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it'll remain incomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.00,0:23:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.96,0:23:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,"That's all that remains of warriors' dreams", huh?{bashou: summer grass}{houtarou goes 'hmm' after this but probably not worth subbing}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.18,0:23:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Later!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.01,0:23:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.14,0:23:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Enthusiasm is no substitute for skill, as you can see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.16,0:23:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you join me for tea?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.87,0:24:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{ED}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.83,0:24:10.59,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,300)\blur2}Let us meet in a blissful dream tonight, let it be our love
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.59,0:24:14.59,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,200)\blur2}Find me, I beg you
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.59,0:24:19.68,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,350)\blur2}We promised to meet, drifting in and out of sleep
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.07,0:24:40.83,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,200)\blur2}This sprouting warmth confuses us
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.91,0:24:51.76,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Don't you understand this feeling yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.34,0:24:57.85,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,150)\blur2}Normally such random glances hold no meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.85,0:25:03.18,ED,,0,0,0,,{\fad(100,450)\blur2}Isn't it the same when making friends?
